__typename": "ApiMedia", "id": "QXBpTWVkaWE6DAABCgABHHOguCKW4AAKAAIcc6C5/xfAGgAA", "media_key": "3_2050158968098447360"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HHOguCKW4AAMy_u.jpg", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 785, "w": 1402, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 1122, "w": 1122, "x": 280, "y": 0}, {"h": 1122, "w": 984, "x": 418, "y": 0}, {"h": 1122, "w": 561, "x": 736, "y": 0}, {"h": 1122, "w": 1402, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 1122, "width": 1402}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 1122, "w": 1402}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/OK40oSPACx"}]}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [0, 4], "text": "AMD"}, {"indices": [5, 10], "text": "META"}], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": {"type": "tweet", "id": "2050035886209867957", "url": "https://x.com/MikeLongTerm/status/2050035886209867957", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/MikeLongTerm/status/2050035886209867957", "text": "$AMD \ud83e\udd1d $META to x3 from here \ud83e\uddf5\nNot Financial Advice!\n\nThe 10 analysts downgraded $META today are as clueless as those that downgraded @AMD in 2023.\n\nThey have no idea what they downgraded. \n\nAMD's partnership with Meta directly supports accelerated AI infrastructure scaling, cost efficiency, and faster model deployment key drivers for Meta's long-term growth. Especially Helios Rack will bring down Inference cost to $0.0003-$0.0005/M Tokens. Read linked threads below to understand more.\n\n1. Why Analysts are wrong?\n\nQ1 2026 results crushed estimates: Revenue $56.3B (+33% YoY), adjusted EPS beat handily (strong net income growth even excluding tax benefits). Ad impressions and pricing powered growth.  33%. Read it again 33% at this size!!!!\n\n- 19% YoY jump in ad impressions\n- 12% YoY jump in avg price per ad\n- 29% FXN YoY revenue growth\n\nFwd P/E multiple should be 27-30x. not 20-21x \nat this kind of growth for this size!\n\nMeta is projected to surpass Google in global digital ad revenue in 2026 (~$243B vs. ~$240B), with faster growth (24%+ vs. Google's ~12%). AI tools like Advantage+ (end-to-end automated campaigns), Reels monetization, and generative creative features are driving higher engagement, better ROI for advertisers, and pricing power.\n\nAI-powered optimizations have boosted clicks, conversions, and efficiency. Advantage+ and related tools have a massive revenue run-rate (previously cited in the $60B+ range in prior quarters). This isn't speculative, it's fueling the ad machine that makes up ~97% of revenue.\n\nMark Zuckerberg and management express high conviction in the spend, pointing to industry signals, custom chips AMD, efficiency gains, and building toward leading models/products. They expect operating income to still grow in 2026 despite higher expenses\n\n2. How Inference cost to $0.0003-$0.0005/M Tokens Helps Meta Accelerate Growth\n\nCheaper AI everywhere = more usage & revenue: Meta\u2019s ad business (~97% of revenue) runs on AI recommendations, creative tools (Advantage+), and Reels. Ultra-low inference costs let Meta run far more AI queries, personalize better, generate more content, and improve advertiser ROI driving higher engagement, ad impressions, pricing power, and growth (already +33% revenue in Q1 2026). \n\nMark Zuckerberg\u2019s vision for advanced AI features across 3.5B+ users becomes economically viable. Low costs support massive deployment without destroying margins, even as capex rises to $125\u2013145B in 2026.\nEfficient inference helps operating income grow despite higher spend.\n\nA full Helios rack packs up to 72 custom MI450-based Instinct GPUs + 6th-gen EPYC \"Venice\" CPUs. It delivers massive scale-out performance (1.4 exaFLOPS FP8, up to 2.9 exaFLOPS FP4) with 31 TB+ HBM4 memory and 1.4 PB/s bandwidth per rack. This enables huge batch sizes, higher parallelism, and better utilization for inference-heavy workloads lowering cost per token vs. smaller or less integrated systems\n\nThe MI450 variant is tuned specifically for Meta\u2019s workloads (heavy on inference, ranking/recommendations). Paired with Venice EPYC CPUs (co-optimized by Meta), it boosts tokens/second while reducing power draw and overhead. Open Compute Project  Open Rack Wide design improves cooling, networking, and serviceability, cutting TCO further. \n\nConclusion: \n\nThe long term partnership between Dr. Lisa Su and Mark Zuckerberg is a powerful catalyst accelerating Meta\u2019s AI infrastructure advantage, powering sustainable revenue growth of 30%+potentially hitting 35%+ in key periods well ahead of most other mega-cap peers. \n\n Dr. Su emphasized: \u201cThis multi-year, multi-generation collaboration... aligns our roadmaps to deliver high-performance, energy-efficient infrastructure optimized for Meta\u2019s workloads, accelerating one of the industry\u2019s largest AI deployments.\u201d Zuckerberg responded: \u201cWe\u2019re excited to form a long-term partnership with AMD to deploy efficient inference compute and deliver personal superintelligence... I expect AMD to be an important partner for many years to come.\u201d \n\nMeta\u2019s Q1 2026 results already showed +33% revenue growth (crushing estimates), with strong momentum into Q2 guidance. This outpaces typical mega-cap peers: Google/Alphabet\u2019s ad growth in the mid-teens, slower overall revenue ramps at many others amid AI investment pressures. The leaderships alignment positions Meta to sustain or exceed 30\u201335%+ topline expansion as AI monetization compounds faster than most peers burdened by higher competition or less direct ad-AI flywheels. \n\nAnalyst downgrades obsess over near-term capex optics and margin noise, but they miss the execution flywheel. The proven ad business + efficient AI scaling via partners like AMD is converting massive investment into durable competitive advantage and superior growth. History favors Meta\u2019s big bets when they focus on user/ad value this one looks set to deliver another powerful rebound and compounding returns. The current post-earnings dip could be a compelling entry for long-term believers in Meta\u2019s AI-augmented advertising dominance.\n\nNot Financial Advice!", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 1, "replyCount": 1, "likeCount": 36, "quoteCount": 1, "viewCount": 7548, "createdAt": "Fri May 01 02:13:37 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 18, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050035886209867957", "displayTextRange": [0, 275], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "MikeLongTerm", "url": "https://x.com/MikeLongTerm", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/MikeLongTerm", "id": "1280587925336530948", "name": "Mike", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1532356424453480448/hGjaGQoQ_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1280587925336530948/1694632431", "description": "", "location": "Tweets AREN'T Financial Advice", "followers": 23550, "following": 392, "status": "", "canDm": false, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Tue Jul 07 19:42:13 +0000 2020", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 9339, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 8589, "statusesCount": 28248, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["1968693172508233889"], "profile_bio": {"description": "LT Investor\nLargest holding $PLTR $AMD $TSLA (75%)\nOthers $XYZ $AMZN $NVDA $LMT $HIMS $BTC $PYPL $META $SNAP $GOOG $PSFE $DIS $GRAB $WING $DKNG $ADBE $BROS $TSM", "entities": {"description": {"symbols": [{"indices": [28, 33], "text": "PLTR"}, {"indices": [34, 38], "text": "AMD"}, {"indices": [39, 44], "text": "TSLA"}, {"indices": [58, 62], "text": "XYZ"}, {"indices": [63, 68], "text": "AMZN"}, {"indices": [69, 74], "text": "NVDA"}, {"in